content:
Ok. So now my old code works without me doing anything more (I like that!)

I've updated the problement statement somewhat.  (mostly removed some variable highlighting, which made it painful to read and wasn't alwaya accurate with regard to the I/O).

And I'm voting to approve.

Good catch!!!
I had actually reverse my book order, so that my top of the book was the worst price
I fixed it and all other tests that had similar issues
You Are right it looks weird, let me check in detail.

I'm confused at trade #4 in the "Multiple Trades" validator: ABC 10 23.45.

It's triggered by a sell order for 10x23.45, at a time where there are already buyers for 7x23.50 and 10x23.45.

It seems like the sale is being matched with the lower bidder, which seems incompatible with the line that says "a trade cannot be concluded for orders that a not top of the book".
Looking forward to see this puzzle on the feed. Great work.
